[1] Cholera - Zimbabwe: WHO
Date: Tue 6 Jan 2009
Source: Government of Zimbabwe; World Health Organization (WHO) [edited]
<http://reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900SID/EGUA-7N2SG6?OpenDocument>


Zimbabwe: Daily cholera update, 6 Jan 2009
------------------------------------------
Highlights of the day:
- 1080 cases and 21 deaths added today (in comparison 675 cases and
59 deaths yesterday)
- 60 percent of the districts affected have reported today (33 out
of 55 affected districts)
- 88.7 percent of districts reported to be affected (55 districts/62)
- All 10 of the country's provinces are affected

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The current numbers are now at 35 330 cases with 1753 deaths (see
full report at:
<http://reliefweb.int/rw/rwb.nsf/db900sid/EGUA-7N2SG6/$File/full_report.pdf>
and continue to increase.

